wiki.text:
'DED' may refer to:

*Dead End Derby, roller derby league in Christchurch, New Zealand *Dedicated
hosting service, a type of Internet hosting *Death effector domain, a signalling
pathway in cell biology *Deutscher Entwicklungsdienst, German Development
Service *District Electoral Division, a low-level territorial division in
Ireland *Doctor of Education, correctly spelled D.Ed. or Ed.D. *Dutch elm
disease, fungal disease of elm trees *[[Dravidian Etymological Dictionary]] by
Thomas Burrow and M. B. Emeneau
* Deferred Enforced Departure, an immigration status in the U.S. similar to
  Temporary Protected Status
* Double error detection, a form of error-correcting code
* Dragging Equipment Detector, a piece of railroad equipment placed on the track
  used to detect any part of the train that is dragging on the ground — a type
  of Defect detector
* De(a)d, the state of the Gentlemen's Lunchtime Association wherein no video
  games are streamed
